sql:
SELECT MAX(effective_date) AS most_recent_effective_date
FROM service_changes
WHERE route_id = 0;

SELECT stop_name
FROM stops
WHERE stop_id = 1;

SELECT city_name
FROM cities
WHERE city_id IN (SELECT city_id FROM users WHERE role = 'transit planner');

external_knowledge:
- The service can be considered discontinued when its end date is recorded, indicating it is no longer operational;
- 'Removing Service' refers to the complete removal of a service from a stop;
- 'Route Modification' implies changes to a route's path or stops but does not necessarily mean removal of the service from all stops on the route.

sql:
SELECT change_description
FROM service_changes
WHERE change_type = 'Removing Service';

SELECT COUNT(*) AS total_removals
FROM service_changes
WHERE change_type = 'Removing Service';
